		</ingredient>
	</ingredients>
	<steps>
		<step>Preheat the oven to <temperature>350</temperature>.</step>
		<step>Grease the inside of two <equipment>9-inch round cake pans</equipment>. Line each with a round of parchment paper.</step>
		<step><procedure>Sift</procedure> together the flours, baking powder, and salt.</step>
		<step>Mix the cocoa, vanilla extract, and food coloring to make a paste.</step>
		<step><procedure>Cream</procedure> the butter and sugar until fluffy, about <time>5 minutes</time>.</step>
		<step>Beat in the eggs, one at a time, until well incorporated.</step>
		<step>Stir in the cocoa mixture.</step>
		<step>Add the flour mixture in three parts alternately with the buttermilk in two parts. Incorporate well between additions but do not over-mix. Then mix until fully homogenous.</step>
		<step>Distribute the batter among the cake pans and level. Bake <time>35 to 40 minutes</time>, until the tops spring back when gently pressed.</step>
		<step>Cool in the pan <time>10 minutes</time> on a <equipment>wire rack</equipment>, then remove from the pans and finish cooling on the rack.</step>
		<step><procedure>Split</procedure> each layer in half horizontally to yield four layers.</step>
		<step>Fill and frost with <reciperef ref="creamcheesefrosting">Cream Cheese Frosting</reciperef>.</step>
	</steps>
</recipe>
